sec.p:
A weaker and eastward-shifted PWC at Smax results in an eastward migration of atmospheric convection and precipitation maxima toward the central Pacific as evident in the Global Precipitation Climatology Centre (GPCC) precipitation dataset (
  
   Materials and Methods
  ) over the period 1950–2013 (
  Fig. 1
   B
  ). Despite the limited spatial coverage of GPCC in the Pacific, the detected pattern is robust and is supported by the reanalyses and the independent GPCP v.2.3 global precipitation dataset (
  
   SI Appendix, Fig. S4
  ).
